    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{-\frac{6}{y^{2}-1}-\frac{6}{y+1}+\frac{3}{y-1}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3}{y+1}, y\ne 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {-\frac{6}{y^{2}-1}-\frac{6}{y+1}+\frac{3}{y-1}} 
      \amp = {-\frac{6}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}-\frac{6}{y+1}+\frac{3}{y-1}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{6}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}} -\frac{6}{y+1} \cdot \frac{(y-1)}{(y-1)} +\frac{3}{y-1} \cdot \frac{(y+1)}{(y+1)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{6}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}-\frac{6\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}+\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(y+1\right)}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-6-6\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)+3\mathopen{}\left(y+1\right)}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-6-6y+6+3y+3}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-3y+3}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}{\left(y+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-1\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{3}{y+1}, y\ne 1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{y-1}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>y \ne {1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
